246. Sic se adhibere, ‘to conduct himself in such a manner.' This last sentence shows what Cicero's meaning is in the whole passage. He means to recommend ‘ lenitas ' as an accompaniment to the ‘ severitas‚' which he has already urged, and he does so here on the ground that it would be even more acceptable in the provinces, where the governor was an autocrat, and there was no one else to appeal to, than it was at Rome, where there were many resources for protection.
